title: Grateful Dead Live at Orlando Arena on 1991-04-08
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) ->KORG AudioGate 4 -> Samplitude Professional v11.2.1 -> FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Walkin' Blues, El Paso, Me & My Uncle-> Maggie's Farm, Dire Wolf, Picasso Moon, Might As Well

Set 2

Eyes Of The World, Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools, Truckin'-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> I Need A Miracle-> Morning Dew, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text:
I am baffled Why isn't this show even liked averagely? This is the epitome of an overlooked show.
Lots to like here.

Overlooked Gem Once again Florida doesn't disappoint. I attended the fine Atlanta run and wish I ‘d trecked down to Disney. Bruce made a difference at this time that was almost entirely positive  (I'm sorry, no one wants to hear The Way It Is [Hornsby’s ‘80’s radio hit that the dead at most thricely waded thru]). But Bruce’s Energizer Bunny energy was infectious. Jerry seemed to feed off the enthusiasm and welcomed his contributions and cues. My guess is the bandmates who’d known and loved ol’ Jer so very long were more than game to participate - shiiiit — Bobby doesn't flub a damn word in a smoking Truckin’ (almost unheard of). For whatever reason these ‘91 Southern shows fucking killed. RECOMMENDED
